         <abstract>
            <p>In this paper, necessary and sufficient conditions are given so that multivariate orthogonal polynomials can be generated by a recurrence formula. As a consequence, orthogonal polynomials of total degree n in d variables that have dim Π&lt;sup&gt;d&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt; common zeros can now be constructed recursively. The result is important to the construction of Gaussian cubature formulas.</p>
          </abstract>
